f Avellino): from the personal name   Bianco   with a derivative form or compound with the personal name   Aniello  ."]},{"name":"Bianconi","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Carlo, Fabrizio, Natale, Reno, Vitaliano.","Italian: patronymic or plural form of an augmentative of   Bianco  ."]},{"name":"Bianculli","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Silvio.","Italian (southern): patronymic or plural form of a diminutive of   Bianco  ."]},{"name":"Del Bianco","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Domenico, Emilio, Gino, Olympia, Aurelio, Aldo, Caesar, Cosmo, Dario, Domenic, Fortunato, Franco, Fulvio, Giovanni, Guido, Mario, Sirio.","Italian: literally ‘of or belonging to the white one’ (see   Bianco  ), hence a name denoting the son, apprentice, associate,or servant of a man bearing this nickname."]},{"name":"Blanco","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Manuel, Juan, Carlos, Jorge, Luis, Raul, Francisco, Miguel, Julio, Pedro, Jesus.","Spanish: nickname for a man with white or fair hair or a pale complexion, from <i>blanco</i> ‘white’.","Italian (Sicily): variant of   Bianco  , perhaps influenced by French <i>blanc</i> or Spanish <i>blanco</i> (see 1 above)."]},{"name":"Lo Bianco","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Angelo, Sal, Salvatore, Antonio, Carmine, Gino, Marco, Riccardo, Salvator, Vincenzo.","Italian (southern; also <b>Lobianco</b>): variant of   Bianco  , with the addition of the definite article <i>lo</i>."]},{"name":"Bianchini","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Italian Guido, Aldo, Angelo, Mauro, Vito, Alessandro, Antonella, Antonio, Attilio, Dino, Donato, Emanuele.","Italian: patronymic or plural form of <i>Bianchino</i>, a diminutive of   Bianco  ."]}]},{"name":"Maria","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Maria  , of German origin but now also moderately popular in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maria Bianco was born in 1115, in Vezzano, Reggio Emilia, Emilia-Romagna, Italy as the daughter of Guglielmo Bianco. She married Marchese Obizzo Malaspina. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She died in 1190, in Correggio, Ferrara, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Italy, at the age of 75."},"et":{"1115–1190":"1115–1190","1112–1185":"1112–1185","1140–1193":"1140–1193","1140–1197":"1140–1197","1160–1210":"1160–1210","1085–Male":"1085–Surnud","da 1160 a 1165":"1160 kuni 1165","1190":"1190","about 1140":"umbes 1140","1197":"1197","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","1085":"1085","1160":"1160","1193":"1193","1115":"1115","1112":"1112","1210":"1210","after 1185":"pärast 1185","Correggio, Ferrara, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Italy":"Correggio, Ferrara, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Itaalia","Pontremoli, Massa-Carrara, Toscana, Italia":"Pontremoli, Massa e Carrara, Itaalia","Vezzano, Reggio Emilia, Emilia-Romagna, Italy":"Vezzano, Reggio Emilia, Emilia-Romagna, Itaalia","Italy":"Itaalia","Correggio, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Italy":"Correggio, Ferrara, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Itaalia"},"fi":{"1115–1190":"1115–1190","1112–1185":"1112–1185","1140–1193":"1140–1193","1140–1197":"1140–1197","1160–1210":"1160–1210","1085–Male":"1085–Kuollut","da 1160 a 1165":"vuodesta 1160 vuoteen 1165","1190":"1190","about 1140":"noin 1140","1197":"1197","1185":"1185","1140":"1140","1085":"1085","1160":"1160","1193":"1193","1115":"1115","1112":"1112","1210":"1210","after 1185":"1185 jälkeen","Correggio, Ferrara, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Italy":"Correggio, Ferrara, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Italia","Pontremoli, Massa-Carrara, Toscana, Italia":"Pontremoli, Massa e Carrara, Italia","Vezzano, Reggio Emilia, Emilia-Romagna, Italy":"Vezzano, Reggio Emilia, Emilia-Romagna, Italia","Italy":"Italia","Correggio, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Italy":"Correggio, Ferrara, Ferrara, Emilia-Romagna, Italia"},"fr":{"1115–1190":"1115–1190","1112–1185":"1112–1185",